social_posts.post_text:
So awesome to speak in @clackamascounty again yesterday and to have my dear friend @usoamissoregon share the stage and mic.
.
Kira's story and mine first became intertwined when her older brother who had connected with me years before after getting a "JustWiggleYourToes" tattoo passed away from an accidental fentanyl overdose. 
.
A sadly all-to-familiar story these days with fentanyl and opioid related deaths affecting hundreds of thousands of people young and old across N America each year. 
.
It was an honour to join up with @usoamissoregon who has been doing amazing things in her community to bring opioid awareness and support.
.
Huge thanks to @crossword_rob + @clackamascounty for making yesterday possible and to everyone at @newurbanhighschool + @ocslacademy for welcoming us into your schools and being such amazing audiences 🤘🖤👣
.
#TrafficSafety #MentalHealth #SuicidePrevention #FentanylAwareness #OpioidAwareness #ClackamasCounty #MissUSOAOregon #JustWiggleYourToes #JWYT #KevinBrooksSpeaker

2023 IS a WRAP!!! 
.
Shout out to everyone from @urbanacademybc @sutherlandgrad2024 @carsongraham_official. Thanks for helping me close out this year on such a high note!
.
150 presentations across 3 provinces 🇨🇦 and 9 states 🇺🇸. This was the busiest year I have ever had. It was also my 20th year as public speaker, and I can honestly say that I love this journey as much as ever.
.
The list of people, schools, organizations, volunteers, sponsors, partners, advocates, fundraisers, etc who make this all possible is too long to list, but if you're reading this, I thank you. 
.
So many of your names and faces and memories from this past year have been scrolling through my mind the past few days. I am very grateful. 
.
I'll be chilling at home for a few weeks with Zeke. Doing a few comedy shows and hanging with family over the holidays. I'll be back speaking January 10th with all of this momentum behind me and a renewed energy for 2024 (it's shaping up to be another very busy year)
.
I wish everyone a safe and happy remainder of 2023. See you next year!! 
.
